so important to ASL morphology. The sign for a given number can be incorporated into an existing sign to give it additional meaning. For example, when signing “month,” one can have 3 fingers extended rather than just the index finger to indicate “3 months” rather than just a month.%0a%3c %0a%3c Source: https://asllinguistics.weebly.com/morphology.html%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
